Plotting transit travel time to the nearest school in San Francisco

```

This map indicates that, generally, accessibility to schools is poorer in the peripheral areas. As seen in the map, the transit travel times to the nearest school are comparatively higher in these areas of the city. This could be either due to poor density of schools in these areas or higher transit travel times, which could be driven by a number of factors, including poor access to transit, inadequate transit operations, and traffic congestion etc.
